❤️ for Easy Weeknight Meals! 
4 Ingredients + 30 minutes!

🌮 night made easy with these oven baked Chicken Chimichangas. Here’s the scoop on how EASY this meal is:

+ Shredded Chicken (I cook 2 chicken breasts in the Instant Pot) but you could also use a Rotisserie Chicken
+ block of Cream Cheese
+ bag of shredded Pepperjack Cheese
+ Tortillas

Blend shredded chicken & cheeses. Roll up in tortillas by folding tortillas or you can roll them (like a taquito). Bake for 8 minutes then flip & bake for 8 more. 

The tortillas will be perfectly browned and crispy and the inside will be creamy and delish! I love to top with homemade pico de gallo, salsa, guacamole, or sour cream! 

Cheers to EASY meals your family will ❤️!

#weeknightmeals #weeknightdinner #30minutemeals #recipereels #tacotuesdayeveryday

When author Sheila Myers reached out to me about her latest book, The Truth of Who You Are, I let her know I wasn't a book reviewer. I love to read, but sharing inspiring words to get others to read a book - it's just not something I'm very good at.

But ignore that I just said that because I HAVE to share this book with you in hopes that you also will love it as much as I did!

"The Truth of Who You Are" is a story set in the Smoky Mountains, which immediately drew me in, during the time of the The Great Depression. It tells the story of how the main character, Ben Taylor, joins the US Civilian Conservation Corps and helps in developing the Great Smoky Mountains National Park. 

But it's so much more - it's about true love, family, and discovering who someone really is by the choices they make. It was such an easy read... I finished in 2 days because I just couldn't wait to see what happened next.

It spoke to me and I hope you will be encourage to read it yourself. You can find @sheilamyersauthor here on instagram on her website [https://sheilamyers.com] and the book on Amazon - https://amzn.to/3kEYC8T

If there’s one thing I still can’t predict as a Dollywood Insider, it’s when the park will be crowded or not. I used to pride myself in being able to figure it out, but it’s a little more unpredictable in the past few years. All that to say, busy days are fine - we just roll with it and do things a little differently. Instead of focusing on rides, we enjoyed the I Will Always Love You photo opps, watched the Wings of America Birds of Prey show, and ate some fabulous food. We ended #SpringBreak2023 with a bang - thanks @dollywood ! #dollywood #dollywood2023 #dollywoodinsider #dollywoodinsiders

It’s almost time for 🐰! My kids ❤️ making these Milk Jug Easter Baskets every year. It’s a great way to reuse the gallon jug and it’s a great craft to keep them busy. They also hold more eggs than you’d think! You’ll only need a few supplies that you probably already have at home:
+ Milk Jug
+ Cotton Balls
+ Glue
+ Pipe Cleaners, Construction Paper, Googly Eyes 

Head to the link in my profile for the full step-by-step instructions on how to cut the milk jug to make these cute Bunny Baskets! #easter #easterbasket #easterbaskets #easterbasketideas #toddlereasterbasket
